Title: To Be Free
Description: Free the baby tigers for Ma Xinyi.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Even if the babies make it out alive, I doubt their minds will be intact. The innocent animals. We must help them!
InProgressResponse: Those predators! These cubs are only their most recent victims. But imagine if we could free them all…
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: The little ones roar their thanks. You have my gratitude, along with this humble reward.

Title: Scourging The Scourge
Description: Defeat Ivan The Scourge for Elder Danya.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: WANTED by Order of Elder Danya: IVAN THE SCOURGE, Grave-Robber, now Lost Behemoth and Utter Nuisance, must be eliminated.
InProgressResponse: WANTED by Order of Elder Danya: IVAN THE SCOURGE, Grave-Robber, now Lost Behemoth and Utter Nuisance, must be eliminated.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Ah! You've done us all a service. The reprobate made a habit of robbing graves before he lost his soul.

Title: Flowers for the Departed
Description: Place the flowers at Skysong Crypt to check if Elder Danya's comrades have found peace.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: It's an ancient rite. Put a flower on a gravestone and if it blossoms there, the soul underneath lies peacefully.
InProgressResponse: Have you placed the flowers at the crypt?
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: You're back at last! Did you place the flowers safely? Did they bloom? How are my friends? Tell me everything!

Title: The Corrupted Streak
Description: Defeat the group of Corrupted tigers for Ma Xinyi and end the cycle.
PlayerPrompt: "Did she come back for her cubs?"
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Wishful thinking! The Corrupted forced her here to lure the cubs back to them. How do we break this cycle?
InProgressResponse: Did you put the darlings to rest?
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Tigers will always have a special place with me…

Title: The Mystery Within
Description: Help Yue study the Corrupted nodule at Imperial Army Campsite.
PlayerPrompt: "Why don't you take a closer look?"
ObjectiveProposalResponse: I have no desire to get closer to Corrupted slime. But perhaps you could examine it? I have a few coins that I can offer.
InProgressResponse: So, what do the Corrupted see in that that nodule?
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Ah, wonderful! Time to study this stone and understand how the Corrupted think…

Title: Treasured Trinkets
Description: Recover Chinese heirlooms from the Corrupted and give them to Yue so she can discover more about her past.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Not even close. The Corrupted take over our land, our people and now our memories. Why'd they need those artifacts, anyway?
InProgressResponse: Any luck with the artifacts? Or are the Corrupted impossible to overcome?
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: I was an infant when I got here, and I know nothing of my old home — except from stories. This will help me learn of it!

Title: Sins of the Brothers
Description: Help Bardroy's sons, Bartolome and Bartholomew see sense and stop fighting each other.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: I don't even remember what they're fighting over, and I doubt they do either. Killed each other repeatedly! I've had it. Go knock sense into 'em.
InProgressResponse: I pray my boys are not too far gone. They may be addlepated idiots, but... they are mine.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Those reckless loons. My plan didn't work! They're still at each other's throats. But I'll find a way to make them see reason… despite this being Lost business.

Title: The Show Must Go On
Description: Get black ink from Void Pitchers so Magistrate Redridge may complete her play about the Empress.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: No, no, no, that's not the answer. We give the wide-eyed masses an idea. A belief. We are more than a community. We are a symbol against darkness!
InProgressResponse: Pray tell, did you get that fungus yet? The theatre eagerly awaits your contribution!
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Splendid! With this, I can complete 'The Empress's Journey' — my script! For the Empress. And her people!

Title: Study In Green
Description: Acquire Dryad Wood for Artificer Long to craft robust armor against the Corrupted.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Everyone says the same. Yet where would she be without the throne she sits on, the shrines she commands? I built them all.
InProgressResponse: Well? Don't you have the Dryad Wood yet? I am waiting.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Oh, I was right about you! Capable indeed - not many make it back alive. This wood will do nicely... The Empress thanks you!

Title: Statuette Stash
Description: Collect four Statuettes as told by handmaiden Zeng, to disrupt the Corrupted ritual.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Master Qi has said every soul that enters a temple leaves an imprint upon the place.
InProgressResponse: Hurry and gather the other statues before it is too late. We can't let the Corrupted get a hold of such power!
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: I'll store these statues carefully. We don't want them to break and unleash... whatever Corruption lies within.

Title: Family Puzzles
Description: Return the puzzle box to Bardroy and discover the prize his sons were fighting to own.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: You helped me previously. I don't mind sharing what’s inside… if you retrieve it. Deal? Still in some cargo the pirates filched from me long time back.
InProgressResponse: Did you find my puzzle box yet? You wouldn't be able to open it without me, mind. In case the greed got you too…
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: So, the contents of this box? Rum aged one-hundred years. A legend of the seas! Caramel. Smoky. As smooth as a lady's glove.

Title: Shrine Cleansing
Description: Cleanse Skysong Shrine for Artificer Long.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Cure the abominable royal child while Corruption infects the land. My shrine needs cleansing and nobody offers to help!
InProgressResponse: Sigh. I knew it. You really didn't intend to help me either, did you? My poor shrine wilts! From the inside out!
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: You saw the shrine overrun with all manner of Corrupted horrors? I was afraid of that. Without cleansing, the Corrupted must have taken it over.

Title: Legacy Reclaimed
Description: Collect Passenger Scrolls from the Corrupted for Yue to study.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Exactly! Apparently, the cabin would have had a list of passengers. I may find other people who traveled with me!
InProgressResponse: Could the other passengers tell me about my life in China? Oh! Don't let them be Corrupted or Lost!
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: You did it! Please, let me see. Hm… According to this, a perfumer called Muthalaly was on the same journey.

Title: The Red Claw
Description: Collect a Crimson Paw from Redclaw for a red dye for Xiang Enlai.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: They're used in the Hair Combing ceremony. And that will protect us as a couple… if she'll have me.
InProgressResponse: You will keep the details of this task between us, correct? I want Yue to think I fought the Red Claw myself.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: The Red Claw! Defeated? You're brave, like Yue. I hope she likes the red string and says 'yes'. Then we'll be married!

Title: Serenity In Chaos
Description: Destroy Corrupted forces at Serenity Monastery. Then report back to Artificer Long.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Gathering intelligence for when the time is right to use it.
InProgressResponse: Did you disrupt the meeting, or were you too busy thinking about what I should and shouldn't have done?
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: The Empress's mind was clouded. I can see that yours is much clearer. I do value everything you've done for me.

Title: Strings of Fate
Description: Retrieve red strings from Dynasty Corrupted for Xiang Enlai and Yue.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Not quite. Yue wants the red strings the Imperial Guards use for their armor. It is tangible fabric. Could you help me once again?
InProgressResponse: Once Yue and I are married, we'll spend our honeymoon in Everfall. I hear they have a never-ending banquet there.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: These are the perfect strings. I can't wait to show them to Yue. She'll say 'yes' to me now!

Title: Revenge of a Playwright
Description: Sabotage the Corrupted operations as payback for spoiling Redridge's play.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Yes… Yes! We've been gentle with the Corrupted for too long. Think therefore on revenge and cease to weep!
InProgressResponse: Let's teach the Corrupted it's NEVER a good idea to mess with the arts!
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: The Corrupted deserved everything you gave them and more. They will rue the day they hurt our Empress and my play!

Title: End of Her Reign (Expedition)
Description: Defeat Empress Zhou Taiying and her Captains. Then report back to Zeng Lingyun in the Ebonscale Settlement.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: I'd ask Liang for help, but his wounds are too fresh. Corrupted Empress Zhou besieges the docks with her 'loyal' handmaidens.
InProgressResponse: I will wish you good fortune. Empress Zhou Taiying was always formidable. Perhaps even more so now in her Corruption…
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: News of your valor has reached us! It was a sad thing to ask of you… but I am grateful. The shipyards are safe. For now…

Title: Justice For The Dynasty (Expedition)
Description: Obtain Dynasty Shackles from Dynasty Shipyard Lieutenants and return them to Liberator Guo outside the Dynasty Shipyards In Ebonscale.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: You stand at the precipice of a critical operation for Ebonscale Reach. The people of Zhou Taiying's Dynasty have been betrayed by her turn to Corruption.
InProgressResponse: Taking these shackles away from the upper members of her court give adventurers and innocents a fighting chance in running from Taiying's terror.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: These devices are truly the tools of an oppressor. On behalf of the people of the Dynasty, I thank you. We will melt these down and make something good of them.
